    • testInverseAccuratelyIsAccurate

      @Test @Order(21) @DisplayName("matrix.inverseAccurately() returns a much more accurate inversion, than matrix.inverse()") void testInverseAccuratelyIsAccurate()
      Generates a series of random matrices (data samples), for each of them finds inversion with inverse() method and another inversion using InverseAccurately(), computes errors for both inversions, and estimates the minimum and average ratio of accuracy improvement achieved by the DoubleMatrix.inverseAccurately() compared with the DoubleMatrix.inverse(). Asserts that the minimum improvement ratio is greater that EXPECTED_MIN_IMPROVEMENT and the average improvement ratio is greater than EXPECTED_AVR_IMPROVEMENT
      See Also:
      • EXPECTED_MIN_IMPROVEMENT
